    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-08-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-08-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="445"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d445">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111Sp1/74</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Spanish Minister of State</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_DLM1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">De Lema</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the American Ambassador</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_WJE1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d445fn1">Copy enclosed in the Ambassador’s
                        despatch No. 791, Aug. 31 (received Sept. 22).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 402</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santander</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-08-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 28, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: In reply to Your Excellency’s kind note
                    No. 57–A of the 6th instant,<note n="2" xml:id="d445fn2">See telegram to the
                        Ambassador, No. 626, Aug. 1, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> I have the
                    honor to enclose herewith two statements<note n="3" xml:id="d445fn3">Not
                        printed.</note> relative to the sinking of the Norwegian steamers <hi
                        rend="italic">Voss</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Tromp</hi>, in whose crews,
                    Your Excellency states, were American citizens.</p>
                <p>From the contents of these documents, Your Excellency can perceive that said
                    ships were destroyed outside of Spanish territorial waters, and that the
                    information furnished to the Embassy, fixing respectively at a quarter of a mile
                    and a mile and a half the distance from the coast at which the above-mentioned
                    ships were sunk, cannot be admitted as exact.</p>
                <p>I avail myself of the occasion [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_DLM1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Marqués de Lema</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
